          "explanation": "Solution\nLet the sum of present ages of the two sons be x years.\nThen,father's present age = 3x years.\nâˆ´ (3x + 4)=2 (x +8) â‡” 3x + 4 = 2x + 16 â‡” x =12.\nHence,father's present age = 36 years. Answer A"
