          "explanation": "Consider the rhombus ABCD. Let the diagonals intersect at E. Since diagonals bisect at right angles in a rhombus.\nBE2 + AE2 = AB2\n252 = 152 + AE2 AE\n= √(625 - 225)\n= √400 = 20,\nAC = 20 + 20 = 40 cm.\nArea of a rhombus\n= 1/2 * d1d2\n= 1/2 * 40 * 30\n= 600 sq.cm.\nAnswer:E"
