          "explanation": "Thecomplementof angle A is the angle which, when added to angle A, gives 90 degrees. The two acute angles of a right triangle are complements, for example.\nThe original angle is x, so the complement is 2x, and together, these add up to 90 degrees.\nx + 2x = 90\n3x = 90\nx = 30°\nAnswer = (B)"
