          "explanation": "Here, n(S) = 52\nThere are 13 cards of diamond (including one king) and there are 3 more kings.\nLet E = event of getting a diamond or a king.\nThen, n(E) = (13 + 3) = 16\nP (E) = 16 / 52 = 4/13\nC"
