          "correctOptionId": "opt-D",
          "explanation": "Let savings in N.S.C and P.P.F. be Rs. x and Rs. (175000 - x) respectively. Then,\n=1/3 x = 1/2 (175000 - x)\n=x/3 + x/2 = 87500\n=5x/6 = 87500\n=x = 87500 x 6 /5\t= 105000\nSavings in Public Provident Fund = Rs. (175000 - 105000) = Rs. 70000\nAnswer is D."
