          "explanation": "C.P. of 1 litre of milk = Rs. 20×2/3 = Rs. 40/3.\nC.P. of 1 litre of water =Rs 0.\nMean price = Rs. 32/3.\nBy the rule of alligation, we have :\nC.P of 1 litre C.P of 1 litre\nof water of milk\n(0) (Rs. 40/3)\n\\ /\nMean Price\n(Rs. 32/3)\n/ \\\n40/3−32/3 32/(3−0)\n8/3 32/3\nThe ratio of water and milk =8/3:32/3.\n=8:32=1:4.\nThus, Quantity of water to be added to 60 litres of milk:\n=(1/4)×60 litres.\n=15 litres. ANSWER : C"
