          "correctOptionId": "opt-E",
          "explanation": "If a new cost is p percent greater than the old cost, then (new cost) = (old cost) + (p/100)(old cost).\nIn this case, (new cost) = 60 cents/pound + (200/100)(60 cents/pound)\n= 60 cents/pound + 120 cents/pound\n= 180 cents /pound\nAnswer : E"
