          "explanation": "Let's assume in 2006 the manufacturer sold X.\nIn 2007 he sold X-5/100(X)\nIf sales in 2006,X= 3.0 million find X-5/100(X)\n(3.0 x 10^6)-5/100(3.0 x 10^6)\n3000000-1,50,000=28,50,000-----> 28,50,000(approx)\nAnswer-C"
