          "explanation": "A and B are positive two-digit integers such that the tens digit in A is the same as the units digit in B, and the units digit in A is the same as the tens digit in B:\nA = 10x + y\nB = 10y + x\nA - B = (10x + y) - (10y + x) = 9(x - y). As you can see the difference must be a multiple of 9. Only option C is not a multiple of 9.\nAnswer: C."
