          "explanation": "Alligation Method\nI PART II PART\n14 (x1) -6 (x2)\n\\ /\nx\n/ \\\n(x2-x) (x-x1)\n2 18\n1 9\nRatio of quantities sold at 14% profit and 6% loss = 1: 9\nQuantity sold at 14% profit = 30/1+9 *1 = 3 kg\nQuantity sold at 6% loss = 30/1+9 *9 = 27 kg\nANSWER:A"
