          "explanation": "x = 3 and y = -2\nx-y = 3 - (-2) = 3+2 =5\nx*y = 3 * -2 = -6\nNow we apply it in the equation 2(x-y)^2 - xy =2 (5)^2-(-6)\n==>2*25 +6 = 50+6 =56\nAnswer : D"
